    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Nashville</placeName>
                <date>May 8<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1853</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <persName>Mr Editor</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Reverend Sir,â€”</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Being a constant<lb/> reader of your truly valuable periodical,<lb/>
                I have perceived that you take a<lb/> lively interest in recording the
                procee<lb/>dings of Jewish affairs throughout<lb/> the world Hence I take the
                liberty<lb/> of presenting to you a brief notice<lb/> of the progress of Judaism
                in<lb/> the city of <placeName>Nashville</placeName> There are resi-<lb/>ding here
                about thirty Israelites, who<lb/> have for the last two years in exis<lb/>tance an
                association for Jewish benef<lb/>icial purposes called (Margen<lb/>
                <persName>David</persName>) Shield of <persName>David</persName> This society<lb/>
                has during the short time of its<lb/> existence acquired <del>f</del> a (Bais
                Hackfor<lb/>us,) Burial Ground and it is in<lb/> contemplation to from it into
                a<lb/> Congregation, for this purpose, they<lb/> have for some time <add>past</add>
                a temporary<lb/> synagogue at the house of <persName>Isaac<lb/> Garretson
                    Esqr.</persName> through the kindness of</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>that gentleman.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Revd Mr Iser</persName> has been<lb/> appointed, Hasen,
                Schohul and<lb/> Instructor of the Hebrew <sic>Sanguage</sic>,<lb/> during the past
                Holy daysâ€”<lb/> Divine Services were performed in<lb/> a very <sic>approbiate</sic>
                manner<lb/> and on the <date>second Passover day</date><lb/> a very interesting
                discourse was<lb/> delivered by <persName>Revd Mr Iser</persName> a gentleman<lb/>
                of high<del>ly</del> Jewish qualifications.</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">The Society<lb/> is also using every exertion to erect<lb/> speedily
                a permanent Synagogue<lb/> and using means for its incorpor<lb/>ation at the next
                Legislature.<lb/> At an <sic>anual</sic> election held last<lb/>
                <date>Sunday</date> the following named<lb/> gentleman were elected as officers<lb/>
                for one year</p>
            <list type="simple">
                <head/>
                <item><persName>H. Harris Esqr</persName> President</item>
                <item><persName>E. Wolf Esqr</persName> Vice President</item>
                <item><persName>Messrs E. Franklin</persName>, <persName>L. Lande</persName> and<lb/>
                    <persName>Louis Sohn</persName> Trustees</item>
                <item><persName>Mr L. Hillman</persName>, Secretary</item>
                <item><persName>Mr Marx Elsback</persName>, Treasurer</item>
            </list>
            <p>Hoping that I have not trespassed</p>
            <pb n="2R"/>
            <p>too much on your time and space</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I remain with high regards</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Your <sic>Obediant</sic> Servant</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">
                <persName role="author">Lem<add>?</add> Hillman</persName>
            </p>
            <p>N.B. Have the kindness to insert those<lb/> Hebrew expressions which I <sic>has</sic>
                written<lb/> in English in the Hebrew Language.</p>
        </body>
